<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-06-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-06-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="24" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d24">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/3722</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at London</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_SRP1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Skinner</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-06-02">
                                        <hi rend="italic">June 2, 1917</hi></date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 9.30 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>It is intention of British authorities to accept manufactures of
                                rubber for shipment via Halifax as satisfying undertaking of
                                American concerns to ship rubber goods only via United Kingdom
                                provided that in all cases such shipments must be made under special
                                licenses to be issued by British Embassy as in case of ordinary
                                shipments to Scandinavia. Applications for these licenses will be
                                considered in usual way and subject to all conditions which affect
                                granting of export licenses in United Kingdom.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_SRP1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Skinner</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>